      "message": "This exact validation pattern exists in:\n\nredfish-core/lib/ethernet.hpp - validates HostName property\nredfish-core/lib/hypervisor.hpp - validates HostName property\nMy change simply extends this pattern to NTP server validation for consistency.\n\nbmcweb server ensures the following:\n1. The Redfish specification requires specific error message formats (PropertyValueFormatError). If the backend returns a generic error, how do we translate that to the required Redfish-compliant format?\n\n2. Prevents potentially expensive backend operations (DNS lookups, D-Bus calls, systemd service restarts) for obviously invalid input.",
